    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we introduce a multitask machine learning framework that predicts the molecular structure (formula and connectivity) of an unknown compound solely based on its 1D 1 H and/or 13 C NMR spectra... we show that our approach predicts the exact molecule 69.6% of the time within the first 15 predictions... we demonstrate the effectiveness of this framework on molecules with up to 19 heavy (non-hydrogen) atoms",
      "asbval:note": "Paper does not name the model 'NMR2Struct'; it is referred to as a 'multitask machine learning framework' or 'spectrum-to-structure model'. The research question is otherwise accurate regarding accuracy metrics and molecule size.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "What are the exact structure recovery accuracy metrics achieved by the end-to-end NMR2Struct model on test molecules containing up to 19 heavy atoms?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:58:56.905071+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we show that our approach predicts the exact molecule 69.6% of the time within the first 15 predictions... Structure elucidation accuracy was tested in the same way as for the substructure-to-structure task, where a target was considered correctly predicted if its canonical SMILES string appeared within the set of 15 predictions upon canonicalization.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper reports top-15 accuracy (69.6%) and top-10 accuracy (from prior work cited), but does not explicitly report top-1 or top-5 accuracy metrics. The paper focuses on top-15 predictions as the primary evaluation metric.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Top-k exact structure recovery accuracy metrics (e.g., top-1, top-5 accuracy rates)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:58:56.905071+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we introduce a multitask machine learning framework that predicts the molecular structure (formula and connectivity) of an unknown compound solely based on its 1D 1 H and/or 13 C NMR spectra... The top section of Figure 4 shows some of the molecules that were correctly predicted, emphasizing that the multitask model can elucidate the structures of molecules solely from their 1H and 13C NMR spectra",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly outputs predicted molecular structures with formula and connectivity as SMILES strings.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Predicted molecular structures (formula and connectivity) for test set compounds",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:58:56.905071+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "During training, we passed the processed 1H NMR spectra through a one-dimensional convolutional neural network (CNN) to downsample the signal into a lower-dimensional space.",
      "asbval:note": "CNN is explicitly used as part of the multitask model architecture.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "convolutional neural network",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:58:56.905071+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we introduce a multitask machine learning framework... First, we show how a transformer architecture can be constructed to efficiently solve the task... Integrating this capability with a convolutional neural network, we build an end-to-end model for predicting structure from spectra that is fast and accurate.",
      "asbval:note": "Transformer architecture is central to the framework, used for both substructure-to-structure and spectrum-to-structure tasks.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "transformer architecture",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:58:56.905071+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card refers to 'NMR2Struct model' but the paper does not use this specific name; it calls the approach a 'multitask machine learning framework' or 'spectrum-to-structure model'.",
        "The card requests 'top-k exact structure recovery accuracy metrics (e.g., top-1, top-5 accuracy rates)' but the paper primarily reports top-15 accuracy (69.6%) and does not explicitly break down top-1 or top-5 metrics in the main text."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 2,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
