      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We treat the substructure-to-structure problem as a language translation problem, where we translate a sequence of substructures into a sequence of tokens that can be combined to form a molecule's SMILES string, recovering the molecular connectivity. Our approach is outlined in the bottom row of Figure 1, where we use a transformer model architecture for this task.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes using a transformer to assemble substructures (molecular fragments) into molecular structures via SMILES generation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does the transformer architecture assemble molecular fragments into candidate molecular structures?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:59:10.549849+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here, we adapt a full encoder-decoder transformer architecture for the substructure-to-structure task.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly uses a transformer architecture (encoder-decoder) for the fragment-to-structure assembly task.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "transformer architecture",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:59:10.549849+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To enable such adaptations and future developments, we have released the code on GitHub and provided the training, validation, and test data on Zenodo.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper indicates that trained model weights and code are released, though the specific mention of 'weights and configuration' is implicit in the code release.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Trained transformer fragment assembly model weights and configuration",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:59:10.549849+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "On the test set, the model achieved an accuracy of 93.2%. Examples of molecules correctly predicted by the transformer model are shown at the top section of Figure 3... Overall, 89.6% of the best incorrect predictions have a similarity to the correct molecule that is greater than or equal to 0.50, with an average similarity of 0.68.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper reports exact match accuracy (93.2%) and Tanimoto similarity scores (partial correctness metric) for the substructure-to-structure transformer.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Fragment assembly accuracy metrics (exact match rate, partial correctness scores)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:59:10.549849+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The test set accuracy as a function of the number of heavy atoms is shown as blue data in the left panel of Figure 2 for up to 19 heavy atoms... To better understand the failure modes of the substructure-to-structure model, we examine the distribution of Tanimoto similarities computed between the model's best incorrect prediction and the correct molecule in cases where the correct molecule was not predicted.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper provides comprehensive test set evaluation including accuracy curves, failure mode analysis, and similarity distributions.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Test set predictions and evaluation report",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
