    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_004/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card proposes testing the model on molecules >19 heavy atoms, but the paper explicitly states its training and testing scope is 'up to 19 heavy atoms.' The paper does not conduct out-of-scope testing.",
        "The card's research question frames this as an empirical investigation ('Does the model maintain...'), but the paper only speculates on scalability in the conclusion without providing empirical evidence.",
        "The paper mentions a drop in accuracy at 18-19 heavy atoms and attributes it partly to limited training data for those sizes, but does not extrapolate or test beyond 19 atoms.",
        "The card appears to propose a follow-up study or extension task, not a task described in the paper itself."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 4,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_004",
