    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chemical-graph-connectivity-validation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Structure elucidation accuracy was tested in the same way as for the substructure-to-structure task, where a target was considered correctly predicted if its canonical SMILES string appeared within the set of 15 predictions upon canonicalization.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper validates predictions by comparing canonical SMILES strings (connectivity representation) against ground-truth molecules. However, the paper does not use the term 'NMR2Struct' \u2014 the model is described as a 'multitask machine learning framework' or 'transformer-based ML framework'. The validation approach (SMILES canonicalization) is semantically equivalent to connectivity graph comparison, but the tool name in the card does not match the paper's nomenclature.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
