    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragment-canonicalization-and-matching/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "After canonicalizing all the SMILES strings using RDKit, the substructure vector for each molecule was computed using RDKit's substructure match functionality against the set of 957 substructures",
      "asbval:note": "Paper does canonicalize SMILES and match substructures, but the primary workflow is spectrum-to-structure (NMR spectra \u2192 structure), not fragment-to-structure assembly. Canonicalization and matching are preprocessing steps for the substructure-to-structure task, not the main research focus. The card frames this as a standalone 'skill' for fragment assembly, but the paper uses it as part of a larger multitask ML framework for NMR-based structure elucidation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragment-canonicalization-and-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Canonicalize and match molecular fragments to standardized representations for use in transformer-based assembly workflows. This skill converts raw fragment inputs into a consistent format suitable for training and inference in fragment-to-structure prediction models.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:02:04.728931+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragment-canonicalization-and-matching/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here, we adapt a full encoder-decoder transformer architecture for the substructure-to-structure task. The inputs to the substructure-to-structure transformer are a binary vector with each entry corresponding to the presence or absence of a specific substructure and a start token.",
      "asbval:note": "The transformer does accept substructure information (binary vectors representing presence/absence of 957 substructures) and uses attention to assemble them into SMILES. However, the input is not 'canonicalized and matched fragment sets' in the sense the card implies\u2014it is a binary vector encoding, not raw fragments. The transformer's role is substructure-to-structure assembly, not general fragment matching.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragment-canonicalization-and-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "transformer architecture \u2014 accepts canonicalized and matched fragment sets as input; applies attention mechanisms to model fragment relationships during assembly",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:02:04.728931+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragment-canonicalization-and-matching/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "During training, we passed the processed 1H NMR spectra through a one-dimensional convolutional neural network (CNN) to downsample the signal into a lower-dimensional space... These features were then passed through a full encoder-decoder transformer for structure elucidation",
      "asbval:note": "The CNN is used to encode spectroscopic data (1H NMR), not to depend on fragment canonicalization. Fragment canonicalization is a preprocessing step applied to training data (via RDKit), not a runtime dependency of the CNN. The CNN processes spectra independently; it does not 'indirectly depend' on fragment matching in the way the card suggests.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragment-canonicalization-and-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "convolutional neural network \u2014 integrated with transformer to encode spectroscopic data; indirectly depends on canonical fragment matching for end-to-end structure prediction",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:02:04.728931+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/graph-neural-network-design-for-chemistry/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we introduce a multitask machine learning framework that predicts the molecular structure (formula and connectivity) of an unknown compound solely based on its 1D 1H and/or 13C NMR spectra",
      "asbval:note": "Paper does predict molecular structure from NMR spectra, but uses transformer and CNN architectures, NOT graph neural networks. The paper explicitly states 'Rather than predicting fragments as an intermediate step, recent work has sought to directly predict molecular structure from spectra in an end-to-end fashion, using deep learning architectures such as graph convolutional neural networks and transformers.' The paper implements transformers and CNNs, not GNNs. This is a tool-name conflation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
