    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/model-generalization-assessment-across-molecular-size-regimes/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The left panel of Figure 2 shows in red the structure elucidation accuracy of the spectrum-to-structure multitask model as a function of the number of heavy atoms... However, this decrease in accuracy is dwarfed by the increase in the problem size that grows combinatorially and thus increases over 5 orders of magnitude over that range of molecule sizes.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper does quantify performance degradation across the 10\u201319 heavy atom range and analyzes failure modes (Tanimoto similarity analysis in Figure 2 right panel). However, it does NOT establish boundaries for molecules truly outside the training scope (>19 atoms). The paper acknowledges this as future work.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
