    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/molecular-structure-ground-truth-matching-and-accuracy-evaluation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For training and testing the spectrum-to-structure model, we used 1H and/or 13C NMR spectra for the \u223c143 thousand set of molecules from SpectraBase predicted using MestreNova,38 using the same train-validation-test split of the molecules as on the substructure-to-structure task.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper uses simulated spectra from MestreNova, not experimentally determined ground-truth structures. The card claims 'experimentally known ground-truth structures' but the paper explicitly states: 'the accuracy of the framework drops from 69.6% to 33.0% when used to predict the structures from 106 experimental 1H and 13C NMR spectra' (passage 9), indicating the training/test data are simulated, not experimental.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "molecular-structure-ground-truth-matching-and-accuracy-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "After an end-to-end neural model (CNN + transformer) has generated predicted molecular structures (formula and connectivity) from 1D NMR spectra. Use this skill to quantify how many predictions exactly match the experimentally determined ground-truth structures in a held-out test",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:03:15.432735+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/molecular-structure-prediction-evaluation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Structure elucidation accuracy was tested in the same way as for the substructure-to-structure task, where a target was considered correctly predicted if its canonical SMILES string appeared within the set of 15 predictions upon canonicalization... Table 1 shows the structure elucidation accuracy on the test set as a function of both the spectral data used (1H and/or 13C NMR)... The left panel of Figure 2 shows in red the structure elucidation accuracy of the spectrum-to-structure multitask model as a function of the number of heavy atoms.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly evaluates accuracy across spectroscopic modalities (1H only, 13C only, combined) and complexity ranges (10-19 heavy atoms). Graph-based metric (Tanimoto similarity) also computed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "molecular-structure-prediction-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Evaluate the accuracy and performance of machine learning models predicting molecular structures from NMR spectra by computing exact-match and graph-based metrics across different spectroscopic modalities and complexity ranges.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:03:28.698864+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/molecular-structure-prediction-evaluation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Our goal is to design a model capable of predicting a molecule's structure and the substructures it contains using only the spectral data as inputs, operating in an end-to-end fashion i.e. taking the spectrum and directly predicting the structure it corresponds to and the substructures within that molecule with no intermediate steps... The highest accuracy of 69.6% (Table 1, third row) is obtained when using both the 1H and 13C NMR spectra with a pretrained transformer for structure elucidation.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly tests 1H only (59.6%), 13C only (22.0%), and combined (69.6%) inputs for structure prediction.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "molecular-structure-prediction-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill validates whether the multitask learning framework correctly infers molecular formula and connectivity from 1D \u00b9H NMR, \u00b9\u00b3C NMR, or combined spectral inputs.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:03:28.698864+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/molecular-structure-prediction-evaluation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "During training, the data set was split into a training, validation, and test set using a random split, with 80% of the data used for training, 10% used for validation, and 10% used for testing... To test the trained transformer model for the substructure-to-structure task, top-k random sampling was used to generate SMILES from a given substructure array with k = 5, and 15 predictions were generated for each input.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses held-out test sets and evaluates on them.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "molecular-structure-prediction-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have trained a multitask NMR-to-structure model and need to quantify its predictive accuracy on held-out test molecules.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:03:28.698864+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/molecular-structure-prediction-evaluation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To investigate the relative importance of 1H and 13C NMR as inputs, we trained two versions of the model using either 1H or 13C NMR as the sole input. The accuracy of the model is significantly better with only 1H NMR (59.6%) than with only 13C NMR (22.0%)... However, the best accuracy is obtained only when combining both spectra, showing that they are complementary to each other in terms of the information they each provide.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly isolates contributions of individual spectroscopic modalities.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "molecular-structure-prediction-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use it specifically when you want to isolate the individual contributions of \u00b9H NMR vs. \u00b9\u00b3C NMR vs. combined inputs",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:03:28.698864+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/molecular-structure-prediction-evaluation/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The left panel of Figure 2 shows in red the structure elucidation accuracy of the spectrum-to-structure multitask model as a function of the number of heavy atoms. In comparison to the substructure-to-structure model, there is a more systematic decrease in accuracy with the size of the molecule, decreasing from 77.5% at 10 heavy atoms to 52.0% at 19 heavy atoms.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly evaluates accuracy as function of molecular size up to 19 heavy atoms.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "molecular-structure-prediction-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "or when assessing whether performance scales appropriately across molecules of different sizes (up to ~19 heavy atoms)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:03:28.698864+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/molecular-structure-prediction-evaluation/005",
