    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/nmr-modality-ablation-analysis/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To investigate the relative importance of 1H and 13C NMR as inputs, we trained two versions of the model using either 1H or 13C NMR as the sole input. The accuracy of the model is significantly better with only 1H NMR (59.6%) than with only 13C NMR (22.0%)... However, the best accuracy is obtained only when combining both spectra, showing that they are complementary to each other in terms of the information they each provide.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly performs modality ablation with three conditions: 1H only (59.6%), 13C only (22.0%), and combined (69.6%), directly matching the card's research question.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "nmr-modality-ablation-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Systematically evaluate the individual and joint contributions of \u00b9H NMR, \u00b9\u00b3C NMR, and combined 1D NMR inputs to molecular structure prediction accuracy by running inference under each modality condition independently and comparing performance metrics.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:04:17.041585+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/nmr-modality-ablation-analysis/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The accuracy of the model is significantly better with only 1H NMR (59.6%) than with only 13C NMR (22.0%), reflecting the fact that 1H NMR contains far more information about the molecule's connectivity relative to 13C NMR, thus playing a more critical role in structure elucidation. However, the best accuracy is obtained only when combining both spectra, showing that they are complementary to each other in terms of the information they each provide.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly identifies which modality drives performance (1H > 13C) and demonstrates complementarity/synergy (combined > either alone).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "nmr-modality-ablation-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill isolates which spectroscopic modalities drive structure elucidation performance and quantifies synergy between them.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:04:17.041585+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/nmr-modality-ablation-analysis/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For training and testing the spectrum-to-structure model, we used 1H and/or 13C NMR spectra for the \u223c143 thousand set of molecules from SpectraBase predicted using MestreNova, using the same train-validation-test split of the molecules as on the substructure-to-structure task.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses paired spectra and evaluates marginal contributions across modality conditions on test set.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "nmr-modality-ablation-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have a trained multitask machine learning model for structure prediction, test set molecules with paired \u00b9H and \u00b9\u00b3C NMR spectra, and need to understand the marginal contribution of each NMR modality or justify multimodal input design.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:04:17.041585+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/nmr-modality-ablation-analysis/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "During training, we passed the processed 1H NMR spectra through a one-dimensional convolutional neural network (CNN) to downsample the signal into a lower-dimensional space. For the processed 13C NMR spectra, since it is a binary vector, we embedded it into a dense vector representation.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly uses 1D CNN to encode 1H NMR spectra into feature representations.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
