      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/top-k-accuracy-ranking-and-evaluation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "top-k random sampling36 was used to generate SMILES from a given substructure array with k = 5, and 15 predictions were generated for each input. Using these 15 generated SMILES, the prediction was considered correct if one of these molecules, upon canonicalization, matched the exact canonical SMILES of the actual molecule.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses top-15 accuracy (k=15), not top-1, top-3, top-5 as claimed. The paper states '15 predictions were generated' and evaluates 'top-10 accuracy' in related work (passage 3), but the primary evaluation metric reported is top-15 accuracy (69.6% for spectrum-to-structure). The card claims top-1, top-3, top-5 but paper emphasizes top-15 and top-10 in prior work.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "top-k-accuracy-ranking-and-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Evaluate model predictions by ranking outputs by confidence score and computing top-1, top-3, and top-5 accuracy metrics, where a prediction is considered correct if the ground-truth result appears within the top-k ranked candidates.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:05:39.426105+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/top-k-accuracy-ranking-and-evaluation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The left panel of Figure 2 shows in red the structure elucidation accuracy of the spectrum-to-structure multitask model as a function of the number of heavy atoms. In comparison to the substructure-to-structure model, there is a more systematic decrease in accuracy with the size of the molecule, decreasing from 77.5% at 10 heavy atoms to 52.0% at 19 heavy atoms.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly evaluates accuracy across different molecular sizes (10 to 19 heavy atoms), demonstrating the importance of assessing performance across size regimes.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "top-k-accuracy-ranking-and-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill is essential for assessing generalization performance of structure prediction models across different molecular size regimes.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:05:39.426105+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/top-k-accuracy-ranking-and-evaluation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "top-k random sampling36 was used to generate SMILES from a given substructure array with k = 5, and 15 predictions were generated for each input.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper generates multiple predictions (15 per input) but does not explicitly mention 'confidence scores' for ranking. The predictions appear to be generated via top-k random sampling, which may not produce explicit confidence scores for ranking. The ranking mechanism is not clearly described.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "top-k-accuracy-ranking-and-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when a machine learning model produces multiple ranked predictions (each with an associated confidence score) for a single input",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:05:39.426105+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/top-k-accuracy-ranking-and-evaluation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Although this sudden decrease could be explained in part by the problem size entering the trillions for molecules of that size, a more likely explanation might be that GDB-17 only contains molecules with up to 17 heavy atoms, while the SpectraBase data set, which does contain molecules with 18 and 19 heavy atoms, is much smaller. Hence, whereas 59% in our training data come from molecules with 17 heavy atoms, only 1% come from molecules with 18 or 19 heavy atoms, meaning that the model has had fewer opportunities to learn how to predict systems of that size.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper does evaluate molecules at the edge of training domain (18-19 heavy atoms) and notes accuracy degradation, but the primary focus is on in-distribution evaluation. The paper also mentions experimental spectra evaluation (passage 9): 'the accuracy of the framework drops from 69.6% to 33.0% when used to predict the structures from 106 experimental 1H and 13C NMR spectra', which is a true out-of-distribution test.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "top-k-accuracy-ranking-and-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Specifically use it when testing out-of-distribution or out-of-scope inputs (e.g., molecules larger than the training domain) to measure absolute and relative accuracy degradation compared to in-scope baseline performance.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:05:39.426105+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/top-k-accuracy-ranking-and-evaluation/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "The paper does not name the model 'NMR2Struct'. The model is described as a 'multitask machine learning framework' using 'a one-dimensional convolutional neural network (CNN)' and 'a full encoder-decoder transformer' (passage 6), but no specific tool name 'NMR2Struct' appears in any passage. The paper released code on GitHub but does not provide a specific tool name in the passages provided.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "top-k-accuracy-ranking-and-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "NMR2Struct transformer + CNN model",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:05:39.426105+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/top-k-accuracy-ranking-and-evaluation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Our framework uses an end-to-end approach... which takes in the 1H and/or 13C NMR spectra and predicts both the substructures in the molecule and the molecule's structure... top-k random sampling36 was used to generate SMILES from a given substructure array with k = 5, and 15 predictions were generated for each input.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms the model generates multiple predictions from NMR spectra and predicts molecular structure (formula and connectivity), but the mechanism for generating 'confidence scores' is not explicitly described. The paper uses 'top-k random sampling' which may not produce explicit confidence scores for ranking.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acscentsci_4c01132",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "top-k-accuracy-ranking-and-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Generates ranked predictions of molecular structure (formula and connectivity) with confidence scores from 1D NMR spectra",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:05:39.426105+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
